data.enText: sleep; a time when sb is asleep

data.chText: 她睡着了，睡得又沉又香。
data.enText: She fell into a deep and peaceful slumber.

data.text: sleep ♦ doze ♦ nap ♦ snooze ♦ slumber ♦ drowse

data.chText: 以上各词均含睡觉、入睡之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to rest with your eyes closed and your mind and body not active.
to rest with your eyes shut and your mind and body not active

data.chText: 表示在睡觉，asleep较sleeping常用，但如果用副词表示睡的状态就用sleeping：
data.enText: It is more usual to say that sb is asleep than that they are sleeping ; but if you use an adverb to say how they are sleeping, use sleeping .

data.chText: “阿什利在干什么？”“嘘，她在睡觉。”
指打瞌睡、打盹儿，通常不是躺在床上：
data.enText: to sleep lightly, waking up easily, often when you are not in bed
He was dozing in front of the TV.
to sleep for a short time, especially during the day

data.chText: 尤指日间的小睡、打盹，通常不是躺在床上：
data.enText: ( informal ) to sleep lightly for a short time, especially during the day and usually not in bed

data.chText: 我弟弟正在沙发上打盹。
data.enText: My brother was snoozing on the sofa.
to be sleeping lightly or almost asleep

data.chText: 我母亲坐在有阳光照射的门廊里打瞌睡。
data.enText: My mother was sitting on the porch, drowsing in the sun.

tr: a natural and periodic state of rest during which consciousness of the world is suspended
example: he didn't get enough sleep last night
calm as a child in dreamless slumber

example.ex: He had fallen into exhausted slumber...
He roused Charles from his slumbers.
example.tran: 他把查尔斯从睡梦中叫醒。

example.ex: The older three girls are still slumbering peacefully.
example.tran: 稍大的 3 个女孩还在安静地睡着。

trans: 睡衣派对(指一帮年轻的朋友穿着睡衣通宵畅谈的聚会)
